This post contains some information about a paper I published in [Infectious Disease Modelling](https://www.sciencedirect.com/journal/infectious-disease-modelling) in early 2020, [*Mathematical epidemiology in a data-rich world*](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.idm.2019.12.008).

The aim of the paper is to provide some ideas about the acquisition and use in mathematical epidemiology models of data from open data sources. 

The paper was supposed to come with an electronic appendix, which at present does not seem to be included. Also, some edition related quirks were added because of the journal style. As a consequence, I have made a copy available as a repository [here](https://github.com/julien-arino/modelling-with-data). My plan is to keep the file there up to date if links given in the paper were to change.
